doc.ContractDescription: IN THE NEAR FUTURE, GEOSTATIONARY SATELLITES WILL PROVIDE AN UNPRECEDENTED PICTURE OF THE LINKS BETWEEN LOCAL AND REGIONAL EMISSIONS AND THE DISTRIBUTIONS OF TROPOSPHERIC OZONE AND AEROSOLS BY OBSERVING, WITH HIGH SPATIAL AND TEMPORAL DISTRIBUTION, THE TROPOSPHERIC COLUMNS OF A FEW KEY TRACE GASES. HOWEVER, TO OBTAIN A COMPLETE PICTURE OF ATMOSPHERIC CHEMISTRY, MODELS TESTED AGAINST EXTENSIVE CHEMICAL FIELD DATA SETS WILL BE REQUIRED. KORUS AQ IS AN OPPORTUNITY TO PROVIDE SUCH A DATA SET IN A REGION THAT IS CHALLENGING FOR THE MODELS ON THE REGIONAL SCALE AND CRITICAL FOR THE MODELS ON A GLOBAL SCALE. TO TRULY TEST THE PHOTOCHEMICAL MODELS REQUIRES MEASUREMENTS OF HYDROXYL OH, HYDROPEROXYL HO2, AND OH REACTIVITY, WHICH IS THE INVERSE OF THE OH LIFETIME. FOR THESE MEASUREMENTS, WE PROPOSE TO DEPLOY THE AIRBORNE TROPOSPHERIC HYDROGEN OXIDES SENSOR ATHOS AND THE OH REACTIVITY INSTRUMENT OHR ON THE NASA DC8 DURING KORUS AQ. ATHOS MEASUREMENTS HAVE SHOWN THAT OXIDATION CHEMISTRY IS KNOWN TO WITHIN THE UNCERTAINTIES OF THE OBSERVATIONS AND MODELS FOR CLEAN ENVIRONMENTS, BUT FOR MORE COMPLEX ENVIRONMENTS, THE RESULTS ARE MIXED. PART OF THE PROBLEM MAY BE THE MODELS OR AN INCOMPLETE UNDERSTANDING OF THE OXIDATION CHEMISTRY; PART OF THE PROBLEM MAY BE THE MEASUREMENTS THEMSELVES. RECENTLY WE DISCOVERED AN INTERFERENCE IN THE OH MEASUREMENT WITH GROUND-BASED VERSION OF ATHOS AND HAVE IMPLEMENTED CHEMICAL MODULATION, WHICH IS SHOWN TO MEASURE THE REAL OH. THIS METHOD WILL BE IMPLEMENTED ON ATHOS FOR KORUS AQ TO TEST THE HYPOTHESIS THAT THE INTERFERENCE HAS ONLY AFFECTED MEASUREMENTS NEAR FORESTS. ALSO, AS WE DID IN THE DEEP CONVECTIVE CLOUDS AND CHEMISTRY STUDY IN 2012, WE WILL OPERATE ATHOS SO AS TO CLEANLY MEASURE HO2. FOR OH REACTIVITY, WE HAVE LEARNED HOW TO OBTAIN 30 SECOND MEASUREMENTS, WHICH IS A MUCH HIGHER TIME RESOLUTION THAN OUR PREVIOUS TIME RESOLUTION OF 3 MINUTES. WE WILL TEST A BOX MODEL AGAINST THESE DATA. THE BOX MODEL WILL BE CONSTRAINED WITH ALL THE OTHER MEASUREMENTS FROM THE DC8. WE WILL ALSO DETERMINE THE MODEL UNCERTAINTY AND PERFORM A GLOBAL UNCERTAINTY ANALYSIS TO SHOW THOSE COMPONENTS OF THE MODEL THAT DESERVE THE MOST SCRUTINY IN ORDER TO IMPROVE MODEL PERFORMANCE.
